# Branch previews are mandatory

This repo auto-deploys to production (`webhosting197.com`) on every push to `main`. To prevent breaking the live site:

- Every code change goes to a feature branch FIRST (`fix/...`, `feature/...`, `polish/...`).
- Cloudflare Pages auto-deploys feature branches to `<branch-slug>.webhosting197-com.pages.dev` (slashes in branch names become dashes).
- Anthony reviews the preview URL before merging to `main`.
- README.md and dotfile-only commits (`.cursor/`, `.gitignore`, `.github/`) are exempt - they don't affect the deployed site.

When Claude makes changes here, the default workflow is: create branch -> commit -> push -> surface preview URL -> wait for Anthony's go-ahead before merging to main.

This rule was forged on 2026-05-11 (across the SlatePress portfolio) after 5+ hours lost to a broken live site from a direct-to-main push on slatepress.co.

## Prerequisite: branch-preview wiring in deploy.yml

For branch previews to actually fire, the GitHub Actions workflow at `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` must:

- Trigger on `branches: ['**']` (not just `['main']`).
- Pass `--branch=${{ github.ref_name }}` to `wrangler pages deploy` (so non-main branches deploy to preview URLs, not prod).

If those two lines are wrong, branches just sit on GitHub doing nothing visible. See sister repo `slatepress-site` for the canonical YAML shape.
